sentences: Maria Grinberg  (Russian: Mария Израилевна Гринберг, Marija Israilevna Grinberg; September 6, 1908 – July 14, 1978) was a Russian pianist.
In 1935, she won the Second Prize at the Second All-Union Pianist Competition.
However, in 1937 both her husband and her father were arrested and executed as "enemies of the people".
In 1970, her 13-LP album set featuring all of Beethoven's 32 piano sonatas was released.
Three months before Grinberg's death in 1978, a review by critic Yudenich in the Sovetskaya Muzyka magazine called these recordings "a true feat of art".
